@startuml followUser
!include ../../theme/theme-dark-seq.puml

title followUser flow
actor User
participant Resolver
participant FollowsService as F
participant ActivityService as A
database DB

User -> Resolver: followUser()
Resolver -> F: follow() : bool

group followRepo.manager.transaction
  F -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> F: follower | null

  F -> DB: manager.findOne(User)
  DB --> F: following | null

  note over F,DB
  Overall flow:
  - if follower/following missing, return false
  - if user tries to follow self, return false
  - if follow already exists, return success immediately
  - otherwise create follow row
  - then log follow activity as active
  end note

  alt follower or following missing
    F --> Resolver: false
    Resolver --> User: data.followUser = false
  else self-follow attempt
    F --> Resolver: false
    Resolver --> User: data.followUser = false
  else lookup existing follow
    F -> DB: manager.findOne(Follow)
    DB --> F: follow | null

    alt follow already exists
      F --> Resolver: true
      Resolver --> User: data.followUser = true
    else no existing follow
      F -> DB: manager.save(Follow)
      alt unique conflict
        DB --> F: duplicate key (23505)
        F --> Resolver: true
        Resolver --> User: data.followUser = true
      else follow saved
        DB --> F: follow saved
        F -> A: logActivity()
        A -> DB: repo.query()
        DB --> A: activity row
        A --> F: activity

        F --> Resolver: true
        Resolver --> User: data.followUser = true
      end
    end
  end
end

== Error rule ==
note over F,DB
If any awaited step inside the transaction throws:
TypeORM issues ROLLBACK, then error bubbles to resolver,
and resolver returns a GraphQL error.
end note
@enduml
